1
00:00:00,600 --> 00:00:01,798
我以为我要回越南去
I thought I was going back to Vietnam,

2
00:00:03,235 --> 00:00:04,544
但他们又觉得
but instead they decided

3
00:00:04,556 --> 00:00:06,758
我对付共产党的最好办法
the best way for me to fight the Communists

4
00:00:06,764 --> 00:00:08,712
是打乒乓球
was to play Ping-Pong,

5
00:00:08,721 --> 00:00:10,936
于是我接受了一个特别任务
so I was in the special Services,

6
00:00:10,965 --> 00:00:12,469
走遍全国
traveling around the country,

7
00:00:12,565 --> 00:00:15,216
慰劳负伤的老兵 为他们表演
cheering up wounded veterans and showing'em

8
00:00:15,272 --> 00:00:16,612
怎么打乒乓球
how to play Ping-Pong.

9
00:00:16,959 --> 00:00:17,854
我打得很好 所以几年后
I was so good that some years later,

10
00:00:17,926 --> 00:00:19,934
军队又觉得我应该
the army decided I should be

11
00:00:20,011 --> 00:00:22,296
加入全美乒乓球队
on the all-American Ping-Pong team.

12
00:00:22,379 --> 00:00:25,834
我们是第一批访问中国大陆的美国人
We were the first Americans to visit the land of China

13
00:00:25,912 --> 00:00:28,450
大约一百万年以来
in a million years or something.

14
00:00:28,528 --> 00:00:31,634
有人说世界和平就在我们手中
Somebody said world peace was in our hands,

15
00:00:31,707 --> 00:00:34,560
但我所做的只不过是打乒乓球
but all I did was play Ping-Pong.

16
00:00:34,641 --> 00:00:37,674
回家以后 我成了全国有名的人物
When I got home, I was a national celebrity ,

17
00:00:37,750 --> 00:00:39,647
比袋鼠船长还要有名
famouser even than Captain Kangaroo.

18
00:00:40,686 --> 00:00:42,617
这位就是福雷斯甘
Here he is, Forrest Gump.

19
00:00:42,689 --> 00:00:44,052
在这儿
Right here.

20
00:00:49,896 --> 00:00:52,864
阿甘 请坐
Gump, have a seat.

21
00:00:52,933 --> 00:00:55,695
福雷斯甘 这位是约翰列侬
Forrest Gump, John Lennon.

22
00:00:55,770 --> 00:00:57,701
欢迎你回国
Welcome home.

23
00:00:57,771 --> 00:00:59,702
你能不能告诉我们 嗯
Can you tell us, um,

24
00:00:59,774 --> 00:01:01,898
中国是怎么样的？
what was China like?

25
00:01:05,147 --> 00:01:07,203
在中国大陆…
In the land of China...

26
00:01:07,285 --> 00:01:09,216
人们差不多什么都没有
people hardly got nothin'at all.

27
00:01:09,286 --> 00:01:11,444
没有财产？
No possessions?

28
00:01:13,926 --> 00:01:18,724
在中国 他们不去教堂
And in China, they never go to church.

29
00:01:18,798 --> 00:01:20,229
也没有宗教？
No religion, too?

30
00:01:22,302 --> 00:01:23,891
难以想像
Hard to imagine.

31
00:01:23,970 --> 00:01:27,233
嗯 只要你肯试着想像 迪克
Well, it's easy if you try, Dick.

32
00:01:27,309 --> 00:01:28,740
几年以后
Some years later,

33
00:01:28,810 --> 00:01:30,741
那位从英格兰来的好年青人
that nice young man from England

34
00:01:30,812 --> 00:01:33,780
他回家去看他的孩子
was on his way home to see his little boy

35
00:01:33,850 --> 00:01:35,747
半路上在给人签名
and was signing some autographs.

36
00:01:35,818 --> 00:01:37,680
完全没什么原因
For no particular reason at all,

37
00:01:37,755 --> 00:01:40,220
有人枪杀了他
Somebody shot him.

38
00:01:42,761 --> 00:01:44,691
他们给你…
They gave you...

